        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>125300</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><choice><unclear>τ</unclear><unclear>γ</unclear></choice>
                            <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig>ελα</orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2a"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraduisible.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Not usefully translatable</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraducibile.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>لا يمكن ترجمته بشكل جيد</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>From those poor rests, we can only guess that line 2 might be part of a personal name such as <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἀρχέλας</foreign> or 
               <foreign xml:lang="grc">Χαιρέλας</foreign>, but none is hitherto attested in Cyrenaica and it would be hazardous to push this forward.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
